reviews.text:
Located near Skyland Town Center and Safeway is this Subway. It's exactly like other Subways except for plexiglass surrounds the entire area where the workers stand.

There's a parking lot in front and despite a small line, I was in and out with two subs and chips within five minutes.
24/7 located nearby America's best wing&Safeway grocer. Good customer service. Not clean property. Ample parking at own risk.

Notwithstanding the bullet proof glass, this place was a nightmare for customer service. Rude, slow, not attentive to the customers request.
I really hate to say this but is a shame when you have people running businesses is a predominantly black neighborhood but treat their cliental like trash. Will never go back there and hopefully no one else will until they change their policies and practices.
Not so clean.. & always a ghetto customer going off about a sandwich. Sometimes there's homeless people

The only reason I end up coming here is because it’s so close to home and open late. Every time I order ahead via the app, I get a call asking me if I ordered. When I show up to pick up the order, without fail, that’s when they wait to start the order. Staff is, more often than not, rude.

DONT GO!!!! The pizza is doughy. They don’t know what, “well done” is. They also went up on the prices for everything, and they won’t even mention it to you. You’ll just have to pay attention. $1 or more on increases on all food. Poor customer service. I won’t be going back there.

This pizza boils is the worst. They’re drivers try to force you to tip them, they shook my pizza and I order the same thing every time I order from them and they purposely messed up my order. The first issue I had with they’re driver was when he came to my door disrespectfully demanding a tip. I call the store back and asked them not to have him deliver our pizza any more, they agreed. The next time I order from them they messed up my order and the same driver shook my pizza. I called them and they didn’t even want to fix the problem. I will not be ordering from them anymore and I will be calling their corporate office. If you can, order from Alabama Ave their pizza taste better and their workers aren’t mean and nasty.

Worst customer service  in the SE area after making me hold for 7 minutes they answer and hung right up. Then I walk inside to 1 customer before me and asked the employee why he hung up. He rudely takes the new phone order and tells me to wait again

I order lasagna they gave spaghetti fish sandwich was burned chicken tenders were super small. Ask for to replace the items the told me to bring the delivered food back on no problem. My bill was 39.26 on 3/2/22 called on 3/7/22 was told money would be returned still no money returned to my card. Called today was told to call back tomorrow. I asked what's the hold up on my money. Was told well call whoever u want

Annoyed I’ve been getting pizza delivered from this location and tonight of a sudden they never delivered to my address what’s funny I have all the receipts when they have them try to tell me it’s another location. When the receipts say Naylor Rd. I’m not letting this go I will be contacting someone about this issue. Like we was really going back and fourth really unprofessional.

First timer. Ordered the Cajun Chicken Filet. The fries were great- I love seasoned fries. They taste unique so it’s not a copy cat if other stores. The biscuit on the sandwich is harder than I like, but the filet is a good size for the price. It’s seasoned well. I love how the sauce pack is as  big as your palm. Also, shoot out to Sherry(?), for making my first time visit a positive experience. Great consumer service!

This place is fantastic! The customer service here is amazing. The manager Christina goes above and beyond to ensure guest satisfaction and that’s truly what keeps me coming back. Always with a smile on her face. She deserves me taking this moment to recognize her. The chicken and biscuits also deserve a review. I absolutely love this place!

The food here is horrible and disgusting. I took a bite and threw my food away. I wasted $8. i had the Cajun chicken biscuit. The chicken was fried hard and burnt. The biscuit was flat like a pancake. The dirty rice was like eating a spoonful of grease. The sweet tea was like the tea bag was never changed. I had to detox after a bite of everything. Never again and won't be returning.

Do not waste your time coming here. All of the employees were eating the food behind the counter, and had the nerve to serve cold food to the customers. How does that happen? This location has no reason to exist. If I could give this location no stars I would.

The employees here aren't very bright. I ordered a three-piece wing combo, a chicken sandwich, a large fry, and two sweet potato pies through DoorDash. The not so bright person who packed my order forgot the pies, large fries, and the biscuit that comes with my meal.

Omg the food was horrible. I’ve never taste nothing like this. I ordered Rasta pasta it taste like mop water. I will never go back to that place again it needs to be shut down. The customer service is just as bad as the food. No coco bread no chicken Pattie’s.

Was looking for a Jamaican restaurant near my job in dc and this popped up. I ordered the "Di Jerk Pan". I was charged $12 online however, when I went to pickup in the restaurant, I was told it would be $16+.
The man in the restaurant informed me that I was supposed to pay online though nowhere on the site indicated this. Seems like there's a disconnect.
I also found chicken dry and as tasty. Don't think I'll be going back. Sorry!

The food was ok. However, they over charged me adding tips that I never approved. I called in the same lady was talking about a button but she's the one that reached over  and pressed whatever. I'm suppose to get a refund still waiting. Poor business practice. Over priced

In response to Rick: I called the store that same day and the day after. I was told it was in the process of being corrected. No it hasn't reflected on my bank statement. If you are aware, then please just correct it. Thank you in advance.

Food definitely was nasty I tried it at the store after buying. Cabbage was over cooked. I ordered curry chicken rice and peas today. I asked for a refund there was clearly a sign that say No Refunds but it doesn’t makes since if the food is nasty. The lady also had an attitude giving me my food and on the register. When I asked for the owner Rick she said he wasn’t there and I asked for his contact info she begin to point to the window like I knew what that meant. This was today 7/29 at 4:30pm the lady ended up giving me a jerk salad which I asked for since it’s a “no Refund policy “ the salad was even nasty.  Just close the place down. Also what is with them covering the prices on the board  and only serving large platters doesn’t makes since to me.
Daughter swears about this place..arrived from California and this is one of her first places to go...Curry and Jerk chicken. Had the fresh plantains ..food is good and spicy...

name: Sardi's Pollo A La Brasa - Temple Hills

reviews.text: The quality of the food has gone down significantly since I started eating here (Central Ave location) almost 10 years ago. The portions are smaller and the food lacks the flavor it once had.  Very disappointing was the salsa Verde. I believe it used to be made in house and was spicy and bright green from actual jalapeños. Now it just tastes like mayonnaise. Don't think I'll order again.
I really like Sardi's, the staff was nice a pleasant.  The restaurant and the bathroom was clean and fresh. The chicken pieces could be a little bigger, however, they were really good. Thanks

I just left there after standing in line, along with 4 other people, longer than we should have.  Whatever system you're using to manage your customer flow and match it with the orders, it does not work.

There was confusion at the registers.  There were 2 cashiers; one of whom could only take cash.  The other one was sipping a drink of something in a cup while ringing in customers, while other customers, including me, were waiting to be checked out.  "is this your food?" while pointing/waving her hand towards an open plate of food.  I'm glad it wasn't given she was handling credit cards, cash and sipping on a drink of something in a cup.   Where was a supervisor or manager?

When my food finally arrived, an employee, who appeared to be trying to manage the food line, apologized.

Beyond the chaotic service experience, my chicken gyro looked like someone literally threw it together.  This is not "thinly sliced chicken."  It was tasteless and I wound up throwing it away.  Having trouble uploading the photos but there were CHUNKS of chicken in the gyro.

I and my family have had consistently better experiences with service and food at the Oxon Hill location.  We've tried to support this one but this is it for me.

Gotta hand it to them, this place Deserves the 5 Stars it is getting! Food is great, portion sizes are wonderful, clean and fun table area with lots of flat-screen tv's on the walls, tables are kept wiped down... Fantastic!

Thankfully the food is better than their ability to spell. I have become absolutely addicted to the chicken, mashed potatoes, and brussel sprouts. However, unlike what's stated on the menu and website, the chicken does not come from Purdue farms. As Purdue University (in Indiana)  is my alma mater I can say conclusive we don't grow chickens. I am quite certain Sardis is claiming their chickens come from Perdue farms (Maryland). Ijs. Either way am in love with Sardis. 😉

Had to return my food twice. It appears that nobody here understands English and I'm not being racist but there is no black or white employees.  The line was to the back of the store. Bad Attitudes were present when complaints were made. This is a whole new store on Good Hope Rd and yet it's starting to be worse than the old one. Oh and the bathrooms were closed but the lobby was open . Smdh

Every time I order the breakfast burrito an ask for the hot sauce I never get my sauce when it’s on the screen. I shouldn’t have to ask for it if it’s up there with my order. If they can’t see that then something is wrong

For a whole week their Cafe machine was down and they did not serve any hot drinks. Just horrible because their White Chocolate Mocha w/ extra Mocha sauce is to die for...come on & fix the machine. I have been craving this drink!

I was oder in this location on the January 09 at 12:37 2023, when I get home I took a bite of my holiday it was hard dry, then i check the order en the Little box to see at what time they made the pie, I see they remove the all sticker and put a new one on top, the most funny part is when i realized the time I buy the pie at 12:37 and on the box paper say it was made January 9 at 1:06 pm come on I know is just a dollar but for me is like your stolen my money my time and my gas, I Hope my feedback can help then to check there’s stuff before selling 😕

I came to this restaurant at 5;55 am! I was yelled at from the door to go to the second window breakfast only! I get to the window two woman are wearing ordering headphones. I place my order, then I’m told to pull up and wait for it to be prepared! The foolery, Bafoonery and Shenanigans are on another level up in there. It is a Spanish employee restaurant with non English speaking immigrants serving English speaking customers! Either cheap labor or putting your people on, in EITHER case.. I WON’T BE RETURNING!

Went through the drive thru at 8:45pm  after the man took my order all I can heat him say was "man I am about to leave I am not doing this s*** anymore". Then he still doesn't turn off his headset and all I heard was the workers in the background chatting it up while I still wait to be told my total and to pull up. I pulled after waiting 5 minutes off because I don't need to give my money to an establishment that's rude and ghetto and clearly no customer service. Not to mention when I do come here the drive thru is extremely slow. Never again.

It took forever to get app to work. Asked a manager to help and was denied.
On top of all that, after finally getting the app to work I ordered 2 sandwich only. They forgot to put a whole sandwich in my bag. Had to go back and wait in long drive thru line again because lobby is closed at 11am.

Service was awful.

The staff weren't wearing masks. I asked fir a manager an some young dirty looking male appeared saying he was yhe.manager. I asked where the older gentleman was that used to manage that store and was informed he no longer worked there. I asked the young manager why he didn't have his "very long" UNKEPT DREADLOCKS pulled back in a rubber band or in a hairnet,  he said it wasn't required. The service was beyond SLOW.  I will never go back there.

This restaurant seems to always be slow and low staffed. The staff isn’t rude but they are nonchalant. They could be more attentive to costumers, especially delivery drivers.

My review isn’t based on just one experience, I’ve come here multiple times to place orders and to pick up orders. Each time they’re slow. The wait time is at least 15-20 minutes each visit, so get comfy.

They have no strategy for orders placed thru delivery apps expect to wait in line, which takes up a delivery drivers time to get to another order.

The actual store isn’t open so it’s just drive thru, hence the long wait.

Plus, They’re always out of specific items. And  there’s is always some homeless people standing nearby asking for money.
This Wendy's has redone its whole staff, the new staff is very quick and friendly. I would definitely go back to them now. Thanks
They need to tear this joint down. Food Trash, customer service Trash, whole building Trash.

The employee had a very nasty attitude. Maybe because it was 🥵 hot. Rude and disrespectful. I love left. I went back the next day to speak to the manager. He straighten it out and offered me a meal choice.

Awesome. The receptionist is very sweet and patient. The delivery service is timely and I mean PUNCTUAL. So you might wanna be at least half way ready 'cause homey does not prefer to wait too long.

The portions are great; a small order can feed, 'eh, about 2 children, just to give an idea. For your 'faithful' chinese carry out restaurant, their food is great. The cost is very reasonable too.

I go to the carry out all the time. I spend a decent amount of money. I just realized that they have no customer service skills what so ever. They got my order wrong twice. They had an attitude when I came up there. They were no help. Rude as hell.

I ordered orange tofu, veggie spring rolls, and French fries. The spring roles look scary. I'm not sure what that is that is burnt inside of the ends. I know for sure that if the inside cabbage and vegetables (since veggies are full of water) is burnt then the outside should be too (since dough has less water in it than the veggies). Even if it isn't something weird in it, it is burnt! It is not okay to serve people burnt food any more than raw, undercooked food. I found a short strand of hair in the rice. The French fries had a decent texture but there were burnt pieces in it.
The orange sauce taste like orange juice mixed with oil and water. I have to say I'm torn about this. I usually find I can't taste orange in the orange sauce at places which not good either. But with this, it is all orange and no seasonings. It could use some celery, ginger, and peppers. Not much salt in it but the orange rinds are still in it. I do like that.
This is the food that gets cooked when training someone new or after the manager goes home for the night. I wonder if they actually stopped using seasonings because the  people there don't like it or to save money. Maybe they have the foundational knowledge of these dishes but not the whole recipes... Sigh. Maybe, I was looking for Thai style cooking...

Update: I did eat the spring rolls after opening and investigating. The veggies inside were burnt because the wrapping dough broke open. I still say they should have redone them. I happen to like a little overdone for my food, and the extra oil penatration. However, that adds a lot of fat and calories. Most people aren't vegan like me. I have to get my Valarie's up. Those extra calories are not good for most people.
The chicken tenders are on point, seasoned well. The fires need salt and pepper. My wait was short, 15 or 20min. But the two young girl ahead of me waited 40min. fyi

I was standing at the register while my uncle was placing an order & saw a 🪳 crawling up the wall! My uncle said something to the staff behind the register, but they did nothing. DO NOT BUY FOOD FROM THAT LOCATION 2863 Alabama Ave SE Washington, DC.

Best American Halal Wings in this close all neoibour,
We love here food and employee of this shop very nice specially barakatullah he is honest and we behaved to customer .

The food here is good but my only problem is the moldy ice machine which people can get sick from. Every time i have been to any American best they blow me off when i ask about it. Pink and black mold.
They are the best food fresh and hot

I order from this Danny's at least twice a month as I work late and don't feel like cooking when I get off. The food portions are on point. The food tastes amazing and their service is stellar. The prices are high but it's worth every penny. Real food, cooked the way it should be. This is the only carry out that I don't mind eating from. You can tell the food is prepared fresh. This location stays busy. I ordered the Chicken cheese and steak and cheese (for multiple people) , two tea lemonade mixes and a large fried rice; when I say delicious ... please believe me.

I ❤️ Panda Express, but I was craving some old school, greasy Chinese food. Since I was out with my aunt running errands last Saturday, 1/21/23, she suggested Danny's. We went to this location near Branch Ave Metro station. I got  medium sized shrimp fried rice, shrimp egg roll & a grape soda. My aunt got Singapore noodles. I paid for our meal. It cost $29.00. Man, that food was good! I had so much shrimp fried rice that it lasted me 2 days! I think there's a location by me in Oxon Hill & I hope they deliver because I'll be ordering from them again real soon!😉
I love this hole in the wall carryout. Reminds me so much of growing up in DC. I never leave Temple Hills w/o hitting this spot.

I went to make an extra rest with this place we just moved here and I heard they had good chicken wings I call this lady hangs up on me I told her I had a big order in the beginning totally unprofessional like don’t they want to make money and it doesn’t even make sense I am still stumped that this woman hung up on me I told her in the beginning of the call that I was ordering for 7 people I am like so mad that my husband moved me from Columbia to temple hills the people here are rude and totally uncouth I can’t believe how the businesses act around here if I could give a negative star I would rude people. I’m so also writing a yelp review. I swear I have never I am still shaking from how badly I was treated
Went to order six wings the lady was real nasty. Am trying to tell her not to cook my wings hard she goes off. I told her I can take my $$$ somewhere else.

This place can be hit or miss. They never answer the phone!! At one point the crabs were tasting precooked alll the time.
But yesterday 8/3/19 I received some jumbo crabs that were actually jumbo. The meat was delicious! I got there at 11 am when they first opened so it wasn’t crowded with the regular rude, loud, drinking folk. Crabs were fresh and cooked to order.. I was completely satisfied!!
Seafood is so bomb omg I’ll never go anywhere else

I woke up with a dope addict's craving for blue crabs one night. After 80% of the crab dealers had stopped hustling for the night, these folks still had product. I went to get my fix. Money well spent.

The place Looks old but there seafood is fresh... I only order the snow crab legs... I can't speak on the rest of the menu... But the price is decent during this time of price inflation everywhere else

Crabs were decent.  I would recommend Jumbo if you can  because females are small. They have good deals on crabs though--I got 2 dozen females for $35.00. Staff is friendly there too.
Fried rice was good.

Nested in a small plaza, this place offers good food and portion size in the area. They're carry-out and delivery only but the food was still good when I got home. The shrimp lo mein really hit the spot, but the beef & broccoli is really the star. I don't like super soggy broccoli in the sauce, rather I like being able to taste the freshness. When I'm in the area and craving for Chinese on the go, this is it.

I ordered delivery this evening and the food was great. I ordered shrimp fried rice, beef pepper steak, beef lo mein and they added a genral tso chicken because of the amount spent. That was a dish I had never tried until tonight and it was outstanding. I am giving 5 stars from my experience.
Good food but watch out they change their prices and leave the old brochures out. They also charge to add vegetables on subs so watch out
Today I ordered kale and beef. The meal looks very appetizing. It tastes very delicious. The ingredients are also very fresh. It is perfect. So I gave a five-star praise

First time eating from there and never again. Food had no taste whatsoever , the shrimp had no season just plain and bland food. Rice was undercooked, food has to be drowned in hot sauce and soy sauce.

Horrible. They always tell women they don’t have any bonus points. This is totally unacceptable and something needs to be done about this. I have several points and this is the 3rd time they said I didn’t. I enter my correct number and then it just goes to the regular screen. If they enter it for you they will say none when you know you have them. I’m calling the BBB on them and file a discrimination complaint

Unfortunately,  I would give no stars.  I spent $90 to fill up my vehicle,  then I used a different cc trying to fill up my mom's car also. After trying twice,  and being told to see cashier (by the system), I went in and Akbar, the cashier, wanted to tell me I needed to use my card inside, as debit.  I told him I wanted to do credit, not debit. He then told me to go back outside and try it again.  I did.  Same issue. He then asked me what I wanted him to do? Don't waste your time or hard earned monies here. The man is disrespectful, and I promise me AND my family will not spend another dime here until it's under new management.
Very clean and nice environment. That guy that works over night always working hard & have a bright smile that will light up a room. I liked his customer service very professional.

I come here to get gas a couple mornings out the week around 530am or so. There's always a sign saying SYSTEM IS DOWN. Clearly this isn't true because you can use the pumps with your card. There are days i only have cash. The cashier is asleep in the back only after banging on the window a few times and calling for him he comes out and takes down the sign sometimes he doesn't even come out....I can careless what he is doing but this is a hugh inconvenience especially when you're trying to get to work. I use this location because its super convenient.

Don’t use your card here for gas your card will say decline, but you know you have money on it... then you’ll get an alert... like I did on my phone saying I spent the amount that it was declined for.

name: Todays Crab House
vicinity: 3510 Old Silver Hill Road, Suitland-Silver Hill

reviews.text: The Jumbo crabs here don’t disappoint! The crabs 🦀 were huge! Simply delicious. Must go! For a half of a dozen, it was about $78. Eyes were rolling in the back of my head before I left the parking lot lol. I had to do a test taste 👅 definitely going back soon.

Today is the last time that I go here. I paid for xlarge crabs and this is what they say is xlarge. This crab size is more a medium size crab and I paid $100 for a dozen. You just never know what you will get here. Some times they give you orders that's been sitting and claim it's your like they did to me last time when I ordered my crab were not hot although I was standing there only for 15 minutes. It's a hit or miss with them. You can go to Mike's crab house and sit down and get very big crabs for $85 a dozen and don't have to question their size.
The place is good. Price is reasonable, seafood and fish is super fresh. We tried the fried flounder, it is coming with cow slaw and potato wedges. Super delicious
I went here on a Sunday. The lady taking orders did not get the order correct(she was chatting with a co-worker) . So when it was time for the food to be ready they only had one.
I ordered 2lbs of Jumbo Spiced 🦐 they were so good. (as always) $26 well spent

Launch is a fun place, and it was an excellent place to have a birthday party! Our attendant was great and the party planner very communicative. The facility has so many fun things to do. The party room is large and provides privacy. We had our party during toddler time, and the food we got (pizza and chicken wings) were yummy! Would definitely recommend this place for fun and a birthday party!

I've been to this location a couple of times lately. So far the food usually is hot, fast and good. But the other day I  got a coffee around 5pm (I really needed it too).  I waited in the drive thru for about ten minutes before I got to order and I only had one person in front of me smh. I ordered my coffee and said 2x no cream (I have a milk allergy). I paid and I checked the receipt  and it showed the right order. I get my coffee and drive off. I'm at least a mile away and I know the coffee is cool enough to drink. I drink from my cup and get a mouth full of cream. They didn't just put a little,  it was so much that the coffee was pale brown. Maybe it's my fault for not checking my drink before leaving or maybe someone could have looked at the order a little closer for accuracy......idk.

I have been to this location a lot (I have toddlers) including pre-covid. Food is generally as ordered and decent considering its fast food. Inside is pretty clean as well as bathrooms generally cleaner than you would expect. Service normally better in daytime when lobby is open as well as better service inside as opposed to drive thru. My only complaint being on atlest 4 occasions i have sat in the drive thru for anywhere from 40 mins to 1 hr 10 mins (from time order placed to pickup) not including times waiting to order and this only happens in the evening, i will not go if its after 11pm here. I dont complain when its 20 mins even though that is still a considerable amount of time, but i do understand and have worked fast food short staffed. Just fair warning, that not always but generally, its a significant wait time for late night drive thru!!

I was glad to see this McDonald's was open around 1 am.  I ordered a crispy chicken deluxe sandwich, it was delicious and made correctly and I also ordered unsalted french fries. The only problem is McDonald's now charges $.15 for any condiments you want extra on your food, wow.

Tiktok @28screwsinmyback

Employees have zero clue or care as to what they are doing.

I waited more than 5 minutes for my mobile order, asked the only employee I could stop to check the status. Her response? “Someone else will check. Wait over there (where I was already standing)”

If you enjoy spending 20-30 minutes to get ice cold food, by all means come to this McDonald’s!

You have got to try the hush puppies with whiting or wings with fries. The hush puppies are sweet with corn bits and the wings and fish are delicious. You wont be disappointed. This is a good hole in the wall spot.

Count your crabs before you leave. I just went there around about 1130 to get a dozen and a half of large males and I get home and I’m eating the crabs as we speak and I only have 13 crabs. I  paid exactly 127.50. I have been calling the number and no one is answering the phone and they are still open because they don’t close till 830 on Sundays. So I’ll say this to you again,check your bags for your crabs to make sure you have all your crabs!
Been eating seafood only from here for years, but may want to keep your head on a swivel!😒😆

My mom and aunt use to come here when I was growing up to get crabs. They're just as good as they were over 20yrs ago.  They have more than just crabs. but he popcorn shrimp, fish, hush puppies, crabs and crab legs are DEEEEELICIOUS😋.  THEY ARE BETTER THAN TODAY'S SEAFOOD AND CHEAPER 😍😍

Their crabs are always good!! But that young Spanish guy hit us with an okie dokie.. He showed us one crab size and by the time we got home to eat them the crabs were totally a diff size.. Lol Chrck your crabs before and after purchasing them...

Not much to say here... Simple, nothing to write home about. Customer service was great. It's clean, friendly and it's fast food. Fish was fried well, the fries are seasoned ok and the wings were average. Great name...

On this my 2nd visit to this location, I ordered chicken gizzards & livers with fries. And, fish & fries. Oh my this food was amazing. I think that sprinkle seasoning is out of this world. They should market that seasoning. The food was hot & good. The employees were happy & smiling. Good atmosphere.

I call to place an order 10:25 am, someone picked up and answered by saying "hello". I had to ask if this was the correct number (strike 1). I placed an order for (5 dinners). Arrive to pick them up they take an hour to prepare although they told me 20 minutes (strike 2). All the fries in every dinner was hard and dry. No coleslaw in any of the dinners and the chicken breast was dry as well (strike 3 and 4). I will never return, such a horrible experience, bad food, items missing from the order.
The fish is the best. The pizza was good. I was surprised to see pizza on the menu. I ordered from GrubHub. I really don't like the chicken legs

I ordered 50 piece of Fish for my step daughter baby shower.  Omg the fish was  cooked perfectly seasoned just right ,
Thank you Hip Hop , let's just say  the guess enjoyed it too the pan was all finished two hours after putting it out.
Great Food, Great Price & Great Location

It’s a place that’s an example of don’t judge a book by its cover. Looks like a regular carry out but the food is really good. I had the Premium Seafood Special and it was amazing. Will be back again!!!

I haven’t even taken a second bite of my food, and I had to leave a review. Just walked over and picked up my Gyro combo lamb over rice with all the sauces. Food was steaming hot, lamb was so tender, just so spiced enough to enjoy. I’m kinda glad the Kisrpy Krunchy Chicken is gone lol

Food is great BUT one worker DIDNT WEAR NO GLOVES while preparing food...especially  the pizza! Had his hands touching all the toppings, he in and out the refrigerator,  touching  the phone, the register and people's money.  The ones with the glove on didn't even once change his gloves after touching everything! HELLO THATS JUST GERMS! ITS CORONA!!

This place is great. We used to order wings once in a blue moon. Now that we found this place we order them way too often and we love them every time. We weren't sure what to expect when we first tried this place but are so glad we took a shot. If you are ordering delivery- we had issues with grubhub and uber eats not allowing us to select bone in vs boneless - but door dash works.

Cajun wings are our family favorite.

Give this place a try!

Listen I don’t usually write these but this place was taking a chance and they did not disappoint. I drove 12 miles away for this and the Philly chicken I ordered with 5 wings was slamming good. The flavor and sauce for the Buffalo wings was well worth the drive. My craving is satisfied.
